<header class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1>The People</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">
      Our Board members advise and steer the organisation, notably through thematic Working Groups (WG).
      A small support team handles day-to-day operations.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

{# Three sections, all using the same card size + grid. Splitting
   Leadership out brings tiered roles (Founding Director / Treasurer /
   Secretary-General) into a focal block at the top instead of being
   absorbed into a 19-person flat grid. Card mark-up below is shared
   via the `person-card.njk` partial. #}

{%- if boardSorted.leadership and boardSorted.leadership.length %}
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Leadership</h2>
    <div class="people-grid">
      {%- for person in boardSorted.leadership %}
        {%- include "person-card.njk" %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{%- endif %}

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Board Members</h2>
    <div class="people-grid">
      {%- for person in boardSorted.boardMembers %}
        {%- include "person-card.njk" %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Support Staff</h2>
    <div class="people-grid">
      {%- for person in boardSorted.support %}
        {%- include "person-card.njk" %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>

    {%- if boardSorted.formUrl %}
    <p class="board-update-link">
      <a href="{{ boardSorted.formUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        On the EISS team? Update your bio →
      </a>
    </p>
    {%- endif %}
  </div>
</section>

{# EISS community — former board members, support staff, and interns
   whose `roleEndDate` is more than a week in the past. The mechanism
   is shared across all three categories: the entry stays in
   board.json (members[] or support[]) but `boardSorted.js` filters
   it out of the active sections and into `pastMembers`. For interns,
   the date arrives automatically through Form question 18; for board
   members and support staff, an operator hand-edits the entry when
   the user reports a departure. Hidden entirely when there are no
   past members yet.

   CSS classes still carry the historical `community-alumni-*` names
   from when this section was titled "EISS community alumni"; the
   visible label was relaxed to just "EISS community" because
   "alumni" reads awkwardly when applied to former board members
   (who weren't students). Renaming the classes was deemed not worth
   the diff churn — class names are internal. #}
{%- if boardSorted.pastMembers and boardSorted.pastMembers.length %}
<section class="section community-alumni">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="community-alumni-title">
      EISS community
      <span class="community-alumni-count" aria-label="{{ boardSorted.pastMembers.length }} members">{{ boardSorted.pastMembers.length }}</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="community-alumni-lead">
      People who have shaped EISS over the years — former board members, support staff, and interns. They remain part of our wider European security studies network.
    </p>
    <div class="people-grid people-grid--compact">
      {%- for person in boardSorted.pastMembers %}
        {%- include "person-card.njk" %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{%- endif %}
